text:
Iowa State at Texas Tech
The Red Raiders remain in search of their first win in Big 12 play following losses against No. 2 TCU and No. 3 Baylor. Texas Tech needs a win to rise from the bottom of the Big 12 standings. A homecoming loss against Iowa State would destroy any momentum Texas Tech established in its three-game stretch of Arkansas, TCU and Baylor. The Red Raiders are 7-1 against the Cyclones at Jones AT&T Stadium and have not lost to Iowa State during head coach Kliff Kingsbury's tenure. Texas Tech needs three more wins to become bowl eligible and it must start with a victory against Iowa State on Saturday. -- Mike DuPont
Who: Iowa State (2-2, 1-0 Big 12) at Texas Tech (3-2, 0-2)
When: 2:30 p.m. Saturday
Where: Jones AT&T Stadium in Lubbock
TV/radio: FSSW / KFXR-AM (1190)
Line: Texas Tech -13 (as of Tuesday afternoon)
